Boddy_etal_reconctruction_sanity_check

Use their dataset, our tree, and make sure that results are in the same ballpark.

Primates Only

boddy <- read.csv("boddy_etal.csv", header=TRUE)
boddy$Species.Name <- gsub(" ", "_", boddy$Species.Name) #remove spaces

library(caper)
## Loading required package: ape
## Warning: package 'ape' was built under R version 3.1.2
## Loading required package: MASS
## Loading required package: mvtnorm
library(geiger)
treez <- read.nexus("Bininda_Emonds_correctedDates_FULLPHYLOG.txt")
tree <- treez[[grep(pattern = "bestDates", names(treez))]] #get the best dates tree
rm(treez)

primates <- dplyr::filter(boddy, Order == "Primates")

name_matchup <- name.check(phy = tree, data = primates, data.names = primates$Species.Name)
tree <- drop.tip(phy = tree, name_matchup$tree_not_data)
tree <- multi2di(tree)
tree$edge.length[tree$edge.length == 0] <- 0.01
primates <- primates[primates$Species.Name %in% tree$tip.label,]



#do this because ace wants a named vector
primates_EQ <- primates$EQ
names(primates_EQ) <- primates$Species.Name
primates_EQ <- primates_EQ[tree$tip.label]

ancest <- ace(x = primates_EQ, phy = tree, type="continuous", method="ML")
ancest
